hless)","category":"mkeyl926","scope":{"type":"full-game"},"mandatory":true,"user-defined":false,"obsoletes":true,"values":{"_note":"`choices` is deprecated, please use `values` instead","choices":{"21d4zvp1":"Random Seed","klrzpjo1":"Set Seed"},"values":{"21d4zvp1":{"label":"Random Seed","rules":"### Submission Rules\n\nFor Pre 1.9:\n\n- sub-25 runs must submit world files\n- sub-23 runs must submit world files, logs, and gameplay audio\n\nFor 1.9-1.12:\n\n- sub-30 minutes must submit world files\n- sub-25 runs must submit world files, logs, and gameplay audio\n\nFor 1.13-1.15:\n\n- sub-20 runs must submit world files\n- sub-17 runs must submit world files, logs, and gameplay audio\n\nFor 1.16+:\n\n- sub-13 runs must submit world files, logs and evidence of past attempts\n- sub-10 runs must submit world files, evidence of past attempts, previous world files (5 preferable), logs, and gameplay audio\n(if using SeedQueue, you must submit 5 worlds before and all worlds after the run)\n- WR Contending runs must contact a mod ASAP, preferably by opening a thread in the #help channel in our discord and pinging moderators, with their Minecraft instances still open and while still recording. Getting evidence zipped in a VC with the runner helps make the process much smoother on our end.\n\nRuns which must submit gameplay audio may do so either through the main submission video or a linked separate video.\n\nLogs can be found in the .minecraft/logs folder. If you are unsure which session has your run, submit logs for that entire day and also the log with the name \"latest.log\"\n\nPrevious world files and logs should be submitted from the instance of Minecraft in which the run was completed. We may request world files and/or logs from other instances, if other instances of Minecraft were being run at the same time.\n\nYou may also be asked to submit:\n\n- A full raw recording of run\n- The editing files from whatever program you edited the video on\n\nWe may request any additional evidence should we believe it to be necessary for ensuring the legitimacy of your run.\n\nPlease don't delete anything until your run has been verified; it may be useful to help ensure its legitimacy. If you have any questions, please open a ticket in the Discord immediately after your run so we may get in contact with you to help assist you in providing any evidence you need.\n\nFiles can be submitted linked in the run description or through the Google form submission (preferred): https://forms.gle/v7oPXfjfi7553jkp7\n\n### Timing Rules\n\nRuns which are not sub-13 in 1.16+, sub-17 in 1.13-1.15, sub-25 in 1.9-1.12, and sub-23 in Pre 1.9 will be timed with IGT.\n\nRuns which are sub-13 in 1.16+, sub-17 in 1.13-1.15, sub-25 in 1.9-1.12, and sub-23 in Pre 1.9 will follow a stricter guideline for pausing, retimed by us as follows:\n\n- The first 5 seconds of each settings change pause are not timed.\n- Pauses directly after an initial load into a given location are not timed.\n- You may request other specific pauses be untimed so long as you provide a reason, the length of the pause, and its timestamp.\n-   Some reasons may include mental health concerns (such as panic attacks), IRL interruptions which couldn’t be reasonably avoided, fixing game lag, and other reasonings that involve things that are beyond the runners control. The pause must also make sense for the reasoning given, e.g. if you have short and frequent pauses and your reasoning was an IRL disturbance and asked to remove all of the pauses, it may not be accepted. If the runner believes most of their pause time would not be counted under this standard for a run not meeting the threshold, they may request a retime.","flags":{"miscellaneous":false}},"klrzpjo1":{"label":"Set Seed","rules":"### Submission Rules\r\n\nFor pre-1.8:\n\n- sub-4:15 runs must submit world files, and logs\r\n\nFor 1.8:\n\n- sub-3:30 runs must submit world files, and logs\r\n\nFor 1.9-1.12:\n\n- sub-1:00 runs must submit world files, and logs\n\nFor 1.13-1.15:\n\n- sub-2:45 runs must submit world files, and logs\r\n\nFor 1.16-1.19:\n\n- sub-1:50 runs must submit world files, logs, and gameplay audio\r\n\nFor 1.20+\n\n- sub-1:35 runs must submit world files, logs, and gameplay audio\n\nRuns which must submit gameplay audio may do so either through the main submission video or a linked separate video.\n\nLogs can be found in the .minecraft/logs folder. If you are unsure which session has your run, submit logs for that entire day and also the log with the name \"latest.log\"\n\nPrevious world files and logs should be submitted from the instance of Minecraft in which the run was completed. We may request world files and/or logs from other instances, if other instances of Minecraft were being run at the same time.\n\nYou may also be asked to submit:\n\n- A full raw recording of run\r\n- The editing files from whatever program you edited the video on\r\n\nWe may request any additional evidence should we believe it to be necessary for ensuring the legitimacy of your run.\n\nPlease don't delete anything until your run has been verified; it may be useful to help ensure its legitimacy. If you have any questions, please open a ticket in the Discord immediately after your run so we may get in contact with you to help assist you in providing any evidence you need.\n\nFiles can be submitted linked in the run description or through the Google form submission (preferred): https://forms.gle/v7oPXfjfi7553jkp7","flags":{"miscellaneous":false}}},"default":"21d4zvp1"},"is-subcategory":true,"links":[{"rel":"self","uri":"https://www.speedrun.com/api/v1/variables/r8rg67rn"},{"rel":"game","uri":"https://www.speedrun.com/api/v1/games/j1npme6p"},{"rel":"category","uri":"https://www.speedrun.com/api/v1/categories/mkeyl926"}]},{"id":"wl33kewl","name":"Version Range (Any% Glitchless)","category":"mkeyl926","scope":{"type":"full-game"},"mandatory":true,"user-defined":false,"obsoletes":true,"values":{"_note":"`choices` is deprecated, please use `values` instead","choices":{"gq7zo9p1":"Pre 1.8","q5v9ev2l":"1.8","jq6j9571":"1.9-1.12","21go6e6q":"1.13-1.15","4qye4731":"1.16-1.19","lx5oek31":"1.20+"},"values":{"gq7zo9p1":{"label":"Pre 1.8","rules":"","flags":{"miscellaneous":false}},"q5v9ev2l":{"label":"1.8","rules":"","flags":{"miscellaneous":null}},"jq6j9571":{"label":"1.9-1.12","rules":"","flags":{"miscellaneous":null}},"21go6e6q":{"label":"1.13-1.15","rules":"","flags":{"miscellaneous":false}},"4qye4731":{"label":"1.16-1.19","rules":"","flags":{"miscellaneous":false}},"lx5oek31":{"label":"1.20+","rules":"","flags":{"miscellaneous":false}}},"default":"4qye4731"},"is-subcategory":true,"links":[{"rel":"self","uri":"https://www.speedrun.com/api/v1/variables/wl33kewl"},{"rel":"game","uri":"https://www.speedrun.com/api/v1/games/j1npme6p"},{"rel":"category","uri":"https://www.speedrun.com/api/v1/categories/mkeyl926"}]},{"id":"2lgzk1o8","name":"Seed Type (Any%)","category":"wkpn0vdr","scope":{"type":"full-game"},"mandatory":true,"user-defined":false,"obsoletes":true,"values":{"_note":"`choices` is deprecated, please use `values` instead","choices":{"5lekrv5l":"Random Seed","rqv4pz7q":"Set Seed"},"values":{"5lekrv5l":{"label":"Random Seed","rules":"### Timing Rules (Internal Only)\n\nRuns which are not sub-11 in 1.9+ or sub-12 in Pre 1.9 will be timed with IGT.\n\nRuns which are sub-11 in 1.9+ or sub-12 in Pre 1.9 will follow a stricter guideline for pausing, retimed by us as follows:\n\n- The first 5 seconds of each settings change pause are not timed.\n- Pauses directly after an initial load into a given location are not timed.\n- You may request other specific pauses be untimed so long as you provide a reason, the length of the pause, and its timestamp.\n-   Some reasons may include mental health concerns (such as panic attacks), IRL interruptions which couldn’t be reasonably avoided, fixing game lag, and other reasonings that involve things that are beyond the runners control. The pause must also make sense for the reasoning given, e.g. if you have short and frequent pauses and your reasoning was an IRL disturbance and asked to remove all of the pauses, it may not be accepted. If the runner believes most of their pause time would not be counted under this standard for a run not meeting the threshold, they may request a retime.","flags":{"miscellaneous":false}},"rqv4pz7q":{"label":"Set Seed","rules":"","flags":{"miscellaneous":false}}},"default":"rqv4pz7q"},"is-subcategory":true,"links":[{"rel":"self","uri":"https://www.speedrun.com/api/v1/variables/2lgzk1o8"},{"rel":"game","uri":"https://www.speedrun.com/api/v1/games/j1npme6p"},{"rel":"category","uri":"https://www.speedrun.com/api/v1/categories/wkpn0vdr"}]},{"id":"68k15rkl","name":"Internal/External (Any%)","category":"wkpn0vdr","scope":{"type":"global"},"mandatory":true,"user-defined":false,"obsoletes":true,"values":{"_note":"`choices` is deprecated, please use `values` instead","choices":{"1dk20rpl":"External","lr35gnol":"Internal"},"values":{"1dk20rpl":{"label":"External","rules":"","flags":{"miscellaneous":false}},"lr35gnol":{"label":"Internal","rules":"","flags":{"miscellaneous":false}}},"default":"1dk20rpl"},"is-subcategory":true,"links":[{"rel":"self","uri":"https://www.speedrun.com/api/v1/variables/68k15rkl"},{"rel":"game","uri":"https://www.speedrun.com/api/v1/games/j1npme6p"},{"rel":"category","uri":"https://www.speedrun.com/api/v1/categories/wkpn0vdr"}]},{"id":"wlexoyr8","name":"Version Range (Any%)","category":"wkpn0vdr","scope":{"type":"full-game"},"mandatory":true,"user-defined":false,"obsoletes":true,"values":{"_note":"`choices` is deprecated, please use `values` instead","choices":{"jqzywv2l":"Pre 1.9","81pjwxn1":"1.9+","klr6djol":"1.14+"},"values":{"jqzywv2l":{"label":"Pre 1.9","rules":"","flags":{"miscellaneous":false}},"81pjwxn1":{"label":"1.9+","rules":"","flags":{"miscellaneous":false}},"klr6djol":{"label":"1.14+","rules":"","flags":{"miscellaneous":false}}},"default":"81pjwxn1